1
00:00:13,118 --> 00:00:14,869
JINWON HIGH SCHOOL

2
00:01:10,049 --> 00:01:11,467
<i>Ms. Choi</i>

3
00:01:12,260 --> 00:01:15,471
<i>was the only good adult I knew.</i>

4
00:01:16,014 --> 00:01:18,224
Everyone gave up on me,

5
00:01:18,308 --> 00:01:21,436
but Ms. Choi did not.

6
00:01:23,730 --> 00:01:24,772
I was…

7
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:29,652
in love with Ms. Choi.

8
00:01:50,882 --> 00:01:52,383
-You're here.
-Yeah.

9
00:01:55,553 --> 00:01:57,597
Why is it so dark in here?

10
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,390
-Here.
-Thank you.

11
00:01:59,474 --> 00:02:02,101
The more alone you are,
the brighter your space should be.

12
00:02:02,810 --> 00:02:05,063
I made too much <i>geotjeori.</i>

13
00:02:05,146 --> 00:02:07,649
You don't like it fermented.
Put it in your fridge.

14
00:02:08,816 --> 00:02:11,027
Do you expect me to eat all of this?

15
00:02:20,536 --> 00:02:22,288
Gosh, this is…

16
00:02:22,372 --> 00:02:23,248
What?

17
00:02:25,291 --> 00:02:26,292
It's tied tightly.

18
00:02:26,876 --> 00:02:27,877
So it wouldn't leak.

19
00:02:28,836 --> 00:02:29,671
It won't.

20
00:02:40,139 --> 00:02:41,724
Would you like a cup of tea?

21
00:02:49,065 --> 00:02:49,983
Sir.

22
00:03:01,077 --> 00:03:03,204
If an action carries emotion…

23
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,626
that's when it becomes violence.

24
00:03:10,169 --> 00:03:11,838
Don't make me tell you

25
00:03:11,921 --> 00:03:14,257
to forget my daughter.

26
00:03:15,633 --> 00:03:16,551
Yes, sir.

27
00:03:18,553 --> 00:03:20,013
I haven't eaten yet.

28
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,223
Let's have the <i>geotjeori.</i>

29
00:03:25,393 --> 00:03:26,936
Is instant rice okay?

30
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:30,690
Do you really want to give
your father-in-law instant rice?

31
00:03:30,773 --> 00:03:33,276
But you made me instant rice
last time too.

32
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:36,112
Cook some rice so it scorches.

33
00:03:40,283 --> 00:03:41,117
You punk…

34
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:43,619
-I'll go buy some rice.
-Don't you have any rice?

35
00:03:43,703 --> 00:03:47,874
If you want scorched rice,
I have some instant scorched rice.

36
00:03:49,125 --> 00:03:51,210
No, I mean…

37
00:03:51,294 --> 00:03:54,630
-I can make it from instant rice.
-I just want freshly cooked rice.

38
00:03:54,714 --> 00:03:56,924
-Well…
-I eat instant rice every day.

39
00:03:57,008 --> 00:04:00,970
<i>The ERPB's approval ratings</i>
<i>have topped 50% for the first time.</i>

40
00:04:01,054 --> 00:04:03,306
<i>In a survey</i>
<i>of potential presidential candidates,</i>

41
00:04:03,389 --> 00:04:07,894
<i>Minister Choi Gang-seok's approval rating</i>
<i>has surged compared to the previous poll.</i>

42
00:04:07,977 --> 00:04:11,814
<i>Some believe he has hit the nail</i>
<i>on the head about the public's concerns.</i>

43
00:04:11,898 --> 00:04:13,399
<i>That's right.</i>

44
00:04:13,483 --> 00:04:17,612
<i>The ERPB has yet to shake the label of</i>
<i>"a group that acts on personal vendettas."</i>

45
00:04:17,695 --> 00:04:21,449
<i>Since the ERPB's key members</i>
<i>are the deceased female teacher's family,</i>

46
00:04:21,532 --> 00:04:23,034
<i>it is likely that…</i>

47
00:04:28,122 --> 00:04:30,166
This is going to be yummy.

48
00:04:34,879 --> 00:04:36,798
Don't you have hot water at home?

49
00:04:36,881 --> 00:04:39,842
I can't be bothered.
It'll be ready by the time I get home.

50
00:04:40,593 --> 00:04:42,470
That's why I said I'd buy you dinner.

51
00:04:42,553 --> 00:04:45,056
Having a meal with your boss
feels like work.

52
00:04:45,139 --> 00:04:46,099
Oh yeah?

53
00:04:47,308 --> 00:04:48,393
Just talking to myself.

54
00:04:48,476 --> 00:04:51,646
Jesus, is it still talking to yourself
if I can hear everything you say?

55
00:04:53,022 --> 00:04:56,567
Do you think
I could just go home from here?

56
00:04:56,651 --> 00:04:59,320
Why? I'll give you a ride.
Do you have plans or something?

57
00:04:59,404 --> 00:05:04,325
I feel like something always happens
when I'm with you two,

58
00:05:04,409 --> 00:05:05,701
and I always get home late.

59
00:05:05,785 --> 00:05:06,786
Hold on.

60
00:05:07,412 --> 00:05:08,246
What's going on?

61
00:05:10,665 --> 00:05:12,583
Looks like they're trying to steal a car.

62
00:05:14,502 --> 00:05:16,295
-I'll call the police.
-No, don't.

63
00:05:16,379 --> 00:05:18,923
They're wearing school uniforms.
This is our job.

64
00:05:20,174 --> 00:05:22,468
Hold this for a second. Here you go.

65
00:05:24,971 --> 00:05:26,722
Then what should I do?

66
00:05:27,223 --> 00:05:28,057
Stand by.

67
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:31,185
But the instant noodles…

68
00:05:31,269 --> 00:05:34,188
I was going to go home
and clean my graphics card…

69
00:05:34,272 --> 00:05:35,690
-Snap out of it.
-Oh man.

70
00:05:37,650 --> 00:05:39,068
You shouldn't have had so much.

71
00:05:39,569 --> 00:05:41,070
What's gotten into you?

72
00:05:49,162 --> 00:05:52,290
Nice! This is fucking sweet.

73
00:05:52,373 --> 00:05:53,791
Here we go.

74
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:54,792
Fuck, whatever.

75
00:05:54,876 --> 00:05:56,085
-Stop.
-Shit.

76
00:05:56,169 --> 00:05:57,920
-Stop.
-Who's that?

77
00:05:58,004 --> 00:05:59,297
Hey, get out.

78
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:00,798
Get out of the way! Move!

79
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,718
-Whoa, what the…
-What is this?

80
00:06:03,801 --> 00:06:05,845
Squirtle's Water Gun?
The Waterbomb festival?

81
00:06:05,928 --> 00:06:07,555
-Move!
-I said get out.

82
00:06:07,638 --> 00:06:10,016
I'm moving now. Whoa, shit.

83
00:06:10,099 --> 00:06:10,933
-I'm going.
-Stop.

84
00:06:11,017 --> 00:06:12,143
I'm going now.

85
00:06:12,226 --> 00:06:14,812
I said I'm moving now.
I don't care. Damn it!

86
00:06:14,896 --> 00:06:15,980
-Move!
-Hey.

87
00:06:16,063 --> 00:06:16,981
I can't see!

88
00:06:17,064 --> 00:06:18,441
-What the hell?
-Stop!

89
00:06:18,524 --> 00:06:20,485
Is he Spider-Man or what?

90
00:06:20,568 --> 00:06:22,862
-Get ahold of yourself. Damn it.
-Hey.

91
00:06:24,822 --> 00:06:25,656
Yes?

92
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:27,992
I'm an ERPB inspector.

93
00:06:28,075 --> 00:06:29,744
What are you doing with that girl?

94
00:06:31,746 --> 00:06:33,414
Wow, the ERPB. Holy shit.

95
00:06:41,923 --> 00:06:43,216
Move!

96
00:06:46,427 --> 00:06:47,762
Inspector, are you okay?

97
00:06:48,513 --> 00:06:49,972
Those damn punks.

98
00:06:50,765 --> 00:06:52,016
Damn it. Move!

99
00:06:56,103 --> 00:06:56,938
That was crazy!

100
00:07:04,445 --> 00:07:05,446
Those bastards.

101
00:07:10,493 --> 00:07:11,369
Im Han-rim, run!

102
00:07:13,412 --> 00:07:14,247
What about me?

103
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:18,417
For God's sake!

104
00:07:21,003 --> 00:07:22,088
Seriously!

105
00:07:22,171 --> 00:07:23,464
Hey, hold on tight!

106
00:07:30,846 --> 00:07:31,847
It's hot!

107
00:07:33,558 --> 00:07:34,850
-He's damn good.
-Passed one.

108
00:07:34,934 --> 00:07:36,936
How am I this good at driving?

109
00:07:38,688 --> 00:07:40,147
-Fucking passed another!
-Fuck.

110
00:07:40,231 --> 00:07:41,107
Hold on tight!

111
00:07:48,531 --> 00:07:51,117
-What the hell?
-Isn't that guy dead yet?

112
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,368
Set them off!

113
00:07:52,451 --> 00:07:53,661
Hey!

114
00:07:54,495 --> 00:07:55,454
Stop the car.

115
00:07:59,584 --> 00:08:01,252
Set them all off!

116
00:08:01,335 --> 00:08:02,628
Fuck, it's hot!

117
00:08:15,933 --> 00:08:17,435
I can't believe this.

118
00:08:27,278 --> 00:08:28,738
Today is epic.

119
00:08:28,821 --> 00:08:29,864
I got them!

120
00:08:31,407 --> 00:08:33,075
Yes, fire!

121
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:35,661
Those punks. Seriously.

122
00:08:52,094 --> 00:08:53,304
Go!

123
00:08:53,387 --> 00:08:55,181
Bang!

124
00:08:58,142 --> 00:09:00,311
Who cares?!

125
00:09:00,394 --> 00:09:01,771
Is he still fucking behind us?

126
00:09:01,854 --> 00:09:03,397
Shit, what do we do?

127
00:09:05,691 --> 00:09:07,443
-What the hell?
-Those little…

128
00:09:09,278 --> 00:09:10,529
Step on it!

129
00:09:18,579 --> 00:09:20,915
This is crazy! Your driving is sick!

130
00:09:25,044 --> 00:09:28,714
-Why are you still holding that?
-She said she was hungry.

131
00:09:35,805 --> 00:09:37,181
Hey, it's splashing me!

132
00:09:40,226 --> 00:09:41,060
Hey!

133
00:09:41,686 --> 00:09:43,562
-Hey! Pull over!
-Careful.

134
00:09:43,646 --> 00:09:45,147
-What?
-I'm not gonna.

135
00:09:45,231 --> 00:09:46,524
Yeah, no. Not pulling over.

136
00:09:46,607 --> 00:09:48,067
I won't. Why would I?

137
00:09:48,150 --> 00:09:49,902
-Get lost.
-Hey, you punk!

138
00:09:49,985 --> 00:09:51,112
He just flipped me off.

139
00:09:52,321 --> 00:09:53,823
-Be careful.
-Damn it.

140
00:09:53,906 --> 00:09:55,074
Passed you, didn't I?

141
00:09:58,828 --> 00:09:59,745
Move!

142
00:10:02,081 --> 00:10:03,541
Whatever, I'm going for it.

143
00:10:09,588 --> 00:10:10,506
What are you doing?

144
00:10:13,592 --> 00:10:15,261
-Those crazy bastards!
-Are you nuts?

145
00:10:18,389 --> 00:10:19,473
Hands off the wheel!

146
00:10:25,855 --> 00:10:27,022
Who are you guys?

147
00:10:32,194 --> 00:10:33,362
We're juvenile offenders.

148
00:10:34,155 --> 00:10:36,365
-What?
-We're 14 years old.

149
00:10:38,909 --> 00:10:39,827
Right.

150
00:10:43,164 --> 00:10:44,373
The police are here.

151
00:10:45,958 --> 00:10:48,502
INCHEON GANGHWA POLICE STATION

152
00:10:48,586 --> 00:10:49,962
We were going this way.

153
00:10:50,045 --> 00:10:51,547
Inspector Im Han-rim was…

154
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:54,759
-Hey, there. Wake up. Are you okay?
-Inspector Im was…

155
00:10:54,842 --> 00:10:58,429
She threw a bike under the car

156
00:10:58,512 --> 00:11:00,264
and stopped it.

157
00:11:00,347 --> 00:11:01,348
Are you all right?

158
00:11:01,432 --> 00:11:03,225
She stopped them from fleeing.

159
00:11:06,020 --> 00:11:07,188
Pull yourself together.

160
00:11:08,564 --> 00:11:10,107
Yun-jin's just drunk.

161
00:11:10,191 --> 00:11:11,609
She had three bottles.

162
00:11:11,692 --> 00:11:13,319
-She drank loads.
-She had more.

163
00:11:13,402 --> 00:11:14,236
She had a lot.

164
00:11:15,529 --> 00:11:18,491
They think we were trying to do
something to her.

165
00:11:18,574 --> 00:11:20,117
We're really all friends.

166
00:11:20,201 --> 00:11:21,577
-That's right.
-Totally.

167
00:11:24,371 --> 00:11:25,706
Are you really friends?

168
00:11:26,665 --> 00:11:28,334
Yes, we are.

169
00:11:29,293 --> 00:11:31,295
So just leave us alone.

170
00:11:31,378 --> 00:11:32,713
See? I told you.

171
00:11:32,797 --> 00:11:34,965
She said we're friends.
We're total besties.

172
00:11:35,049 --> 00:11:36,300
-Exactly.
-Be quiet, punk!

173
00:11:36,383 --> 00:11:38,469
You've committed car theft,
unlicensed driving,

174
00:11:38,552 --> 00:11:39,804
and traffic violations!

175
00:11:39,887 --> 00:11:42,223
-I'm sorry, sir.
-I'm sorry, sir.

176
00:11:42,306 --> 00:11:45,810
But the engine was running,
and we just got in out of curiosity.

177
00:11:45,893 --> 00:11:47,645
That's right. It's our hormones.

178
00:11:47,728 --> 00:11:49,980
We're impulsive.
It's what happens at our age.

179
00:11:50,064 --> 00:11:51,065
-It's our age.
-Yeah.

180
00:11:51,148 --> 00:11:55,110
We're juvenile offenders for a reason.
We're really sorry.

181
00:11:55,611 --> 00:11:56,737
We're sorry.

182
00:11:56,821 --> 00:11:58,364
-We're sorry!
-We're sorry!

183
00:11:58,447 --> 00:12:01,200
-Is that how you show you're sorry?
-We're sorry!

184
00:12:01,283 --> 00:12:02,952
Im Han-rim, don't.

185
00:12:04,370 --> 00:12:06,747
They know they won't be punished.

186
00:12:06,831 --> 00:12:07,873
That's correct.

187
00:12:07,957 --> 00:12:10,292
They've been here multiple times already.

188
00:12:10,376 --> 00:12:14,046
They know the police can't touch them,
as long as they play stupid,

189
00:12:14,129 --> 00:12:15,881
because they're underage.

190
00:12:15,965 --> 00:12:17,716
They know the law too well. Sit still.

191
00:12:18,843 --> 00:12:22,555
-Did you call the parents?
-Yes, but they'll be a while.

192
00:12:22,638 --> 00:12:24,723
Our homeroom teacher said
he'd come right away.

193
00:12:25,391 --> 00:12:27,142
-Hand them over when he arrives.
-Okay.

194
00:12:27,643 --> 00:12:28,978
-Chief.
-Yes?

195
00:12:30,688 --> 00:12:32,147
What happens now?

196
00:12:32,231 --> 00:12:35,776
Serious cases go to juvenile court
and protective dispositions issued.

197
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:38,571
But for a case like this,
we let them off with a warning.

198
00:12:39,864 --> 00:12:42,992
I heard there's nothing
the school can do either.

199
00:12:45,119 --> 00:12:45,953
Here he comes.

200
00:12:46,537 --> 00:12:49,081
-You can hear from him directly.
-Hello, Mr. Lee.

201
00:12:51,584 --> 00:12:53,669
CUSTODY HANDOVER CONFIRMATION FORM

202
00:13:05,139 --> 00:13:06,557
We'll be on our way now.

203
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:09,894
Come and see me first thing tomorrow.
We'll talk more then.

204
00:13:09,977 --> 00:13:10,811
-Okay.
-Thank you.

205
00:13:10,895 --> 00:13:11,812
We appreciate you.

206
00:13:11,896 --> 00:13:12,938
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

207
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:16,817
-Goodbye.
-Thank you.

208
00:13:16,901 --> 00:13:17,818
Get her home safe.

209
00:13:17,902 --> 00:13:19,111
-Goodbye, sir.
-Take care.

210
00:13:23,282 --> 00:13:24,408
It's unsettling, right?

211
00:13:24,992 --> 00:13:27,161
Even I can't get used to
the way they speak.

212
00:13:27,244 --> 00:13:29,163
I hear you're from the ERPB?

213
00:13:29,246 --> 00:13:30,080
Yes.

214
00:13:30,581 --> 00:13:31,832
I'm Inspector Na Hwa-jin.

215
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:34,501
Excuse me.

216
00:13:35,628 --> 00:13:38,881
I'm afraid you two will have to write
another statement.

217
00:13:38,964 --> 00:13:40,966
Those punks reported you both.

218
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,635
For what?

219
00:13:42,718 --> 00:13:43,886
For child abuse.

220
00:13:43,969 --> 00:13:46,972
You can report it
through the app these days, so…

221
00:13:47,681 --> 00:13:48,641
Damn it.

222
00:13:50,643 --> 00:13:53,938
I'm sorry.
I should have taught them better.

223
00:13:54,021 --> 00:13:56,357
Not at all. It's not for you to apologize.

224
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,609
It's embarrassing
to say this as a teacher,

225
00:13:59,109 --> 00:14:01,195
but the school is a mess because of them.

226
00:14:01,278 --> 00:14:05,658
They know all too well
that adults can't do anything to them.

227
00:14:07,952 --> 00:14:09,745
What about the school rules?

228
00:14:09,828 --> 00:14:13,207
They say they're juvenile offenders.
Do you think rules will work on them?

229
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:14,875
It'll be hard to expel them too

230
00:14:14,959 --> 00:14:18,003
because middle school education
is mandatory.

231
00:14:21,006 --> 00:14:21,840
Sir?

232
00:14:25,177 --> 00:14:26,553
<i>Juvenile offenders played you?</i>

233
00:14:27,471 --> 00:14:28,347
Yes, sir.

234
00:14:29,139 --> 00:14:32,559
I did hear that "juvenile offender"
is like a title from the heavens.

235
00:14:32,643 --> 00:14:35,354
I guess former special forces
are no match for them either.

236
00:14:36,397 --> 00:14:38,607
I want to too!

237
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:42,695
Who are they?

238
00:14:43,988 --> 00:14:46,448
It's them. The invincible 14-year-olds.

239
00:14:47,116 --> 00:14:48,200
Bye.

240
00:14:50,077 --> 00:14:50,995
Shit.

241
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:56,583
Bye!

242
00:14:56,667 --> 00:14:58,711
This is fun. Yes, fun indeed.

243
00:14:58,794 --> 00:15:01,088
-Did you say Hyeonjin Middle School?
-Yes, sir.

244
00:15:01,171 --> 00:15:02,840
Report to work there from tomorrow.

245
00:15:08,929 --> 00:15:11,682
HYEONJIN MIDDLE SCHOOL

246
00:15:14,435 --> 00:15:16,186
Jung Seung-jin!

247
00:15:16,687 --> 00:15:17,521
-Hey.
-Yeah.

248
00:15:17,604 --> 00:15:19,106
Why don't you say hi these days?

249
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:22,484
Why the look?

250
00:15:22,568 --> 00:15:24,403
-Did I hit you?
-No.

251
00:15:24,486 --> 00:15:25,821
Yes, I did, you dumbass.

252
00:15:25,904 --> 00:15:27,865
-You're here early.
-Damn it.

253
00:15:27,948 --> 00:15:28,949
Oh, hello.

254
00:15:29,033 --> 00:15:29,867
Hello.

255
00:15:30,617 --> 00:15:31,493
What's your name?

256
00:15:32,327 --> 00:15:33,328
Jung Seung-jin.

257
00:15:33,412 --> 00:15:35,289
Okay, Seung-jin. Get to class.

258
00:15:37,332 --> 00:15:39,168
See you later. Put my bag on my desk.

259
00:15:39,668 --> 00:15:41,253
You guys are so diligent.

260
00:15:41,336 --> 00:15:43,255
You should skip school once in a while

261
00:15:43,338 --> 00:15:46,258
so the other kids can breathe,
don't you think?

262
