00:49:49,508 --> 00:49:50,342
Understood?

794
00:49:51,134 --> 00:49:52,844
-Carry on.
-Back to positions.

795
00:49:52,928 --> 00:49:53,762
Turn around.

796
00:49:53,845 --> 00:49:56,681
-Stand against the wall.
-Face forward. Raise your arms.

797
00:49:57,265 --> 00:49:58,517
-Hands on head.
-Eyes ahead.

798
00:49:58,600 --> 00:50:00,185
Stand against the wall.

799
00:50:00,685 --> 00:50:01,770
What are you doing?

800
00:50:01,853 --> 00:50:03,105
Hands on your head.

801
00:50:13,824 --> 00:50:15,033
Out of the way!

802
00:50:20,497 --> 00:50:23,125
I'm already here
serving the maximum possible sentence,

803
00:50:23,208 --> 00:50:25,210
so killing you won't change a thing.

804
00:50:25,293 --> 00:50:26,670
Inmate 1397, get off him!

805
00:50:29,172 --> 00:50:30,799
Get inside!

806
00:50:30,882 --> 00:50:32,843
From now on, this place is hell,

807
00:50:32,926 --> 00:50:34,427
and I'll make sure to find you.

808
00:50:34,511 --> 00:50:36,972
Let's play hide and seek all day long.

809
00:50:37,055 --> 00:50:38,181
Stay still!

810
00:50:38,723 --> 00:50:40,600
There are lots like me here.

811
00:50:43,103 --> 00:50:45,105
Right, guys?

812
00:50:45,188 --> 00:50:47,149
Right? Aren't I right?

813
00:50:47,232 --> 00:50:48,358
Right?

814
00:51:06,001 --> 00:51:07,502
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

815
00:51:07,586 --> 00:51:09,296
The worst human rights violators!

816
00:51:09,379 --> 00:51:11,256
The ERPB must apologize!

817
00:51:11,339 --> 00:51:13,466
Apologize!

818
00:51:13,550 --> 00:51:15,135
The worst human rights violators!

819
00:51:15,218 --> 00:51:16,178
Hey, he's here!

820
00:51:16,261 --> 00:51:18,263
Minister!

821
00:51:19,264 --> 00:51:21,391
Just a moment, Minister!

822
00:51:22,017 --> 00:51:25,228
Minister!

823
00:51:25,312 --> 00:51:27,230
-Minister.
-Just stop for a moment!

824
00:51:27,314 --> 00:51:29,149
-Minister!
-Hey!

825
00:51:29,649 --> 00:51:30,942
I said stop!

826
00:51:31,443 --> 00:51:32,402
Hold on, Minister!

827
00:51:32,485 --> 00:51:33,528
-Minister!
-Sir!

828
00:51:33,612 --> 00:51:35,488
-Wait a moment!
-Sir!

829
00:51:35,572 --> 00:51:37,240
-Minister!
-Get out of the way!

830
00:51:37,324 --> 00:51:38,158
Just a moment.

831
00:51:38,241 --> 00:51:39,576
Minister, just a moment.

832
00:51:39,659 --> 00:51:42,537
Is it true
that you sent our children to prison?

833
00:51:43,455 --> 00:51:44,873
Yes, that's right.

834
00:51:44,956 --> 00:51:47,459
How could you send
those young children to prison?

835
00:51:47,542 --> 00:51:49,502
It's a field trip.

836
00:51:50,086 --> 00:51:51,588
They'll end up there eventually.

837
00:51:51,671 --> 00:51:52,589
-What?
-Ridiculous.

838
00:51:52,672 --> 00:51:54,257
-Are you kidding me?
-What nonsense.

839
00:51:54,341 --> 00:51:57,219
How could you?
You didn't even get our permission!

840
00:51:57,302 --> 00:51:59,804
Would you have allowed it if we had asked?

841
00:51:59,888 --> 00:52:01,806
-What?
-You should've at least let us know!

842
00:52:02,390 --> 00:52:04,226
I seriously can't believe this guy.

843
00:52:04,809 --> 00:52:06,353
This is driving me nuts.

844
00:52:06,436 --> 00:52:07,938
Great detail there.

845
00:52:08,813 --> 00:52:10,232
Why didn't you write in detail

846
00:52:10,315 --> 00:52:12,734
what your kids did
and where they were taken

847
00:52:12,817 --> 00:52:14,361
on those protest signs?

848
00:52:14,444 --> 00:52:15,528
-Excuse me?
-Seriously?

849
00:52:15,612 --> 00:52:16,780
I can't believe this.

850
00:52:16,863 --> 00:52:19,491
Goodness, where do you get the nerve?

851
00:52:19,574 --> 00:52:20,742
Excuse me, mister.

852
00:52:20,825 --> 00:52:24,579
I'll do whatever it takes to drag you down
from there, so be ready for it.

853
00:52:24,663 --> 00:52:28,041
Being a minister isn't all that
in this day and age.

854
00:52:28,124 --> 00:52:29,876
Forget it. Don't bother.

855
00:52:29,960 --> 00:52:33,380
Ji-ung's mom, let's go to the press
and bring this to the National Assembly.

856
00:52:33,463 --> 00:52:34,839
-That's perfect.
-Sounds great.

857
00:52:34,923 --> 00:52:36,007
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

858
00:52:36,091 --> 00:52:38,677
No need for that.
Come to the children's school tomorrow.

859
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:41,638
Why? Do we have to come
just because you tell us to?

860
00:52:41,721 --> 00:52:44,349
It will be the last chance
to see your children.

861
00:52:44,849 --> 00:52:46,101
So do as you please.

862
00:52:46,184 --> 00:52:47,644
-What did you say?
-What?

863
00:52:47,727 --> 00:52:49,729
-What do you mean?
-What last chance?

864
00:52:49,813 --> 00:52:51,523
-What last chance?
-Wait, come back!

865
00:52:51,606 --> 00:52:52,524
Minister!

866
00:53:12,335 --> 00:53:13,420
Go inside.

867
00:53:13,503 --> 00:53:14,921
-Mom.
-It's Dad. Dad!

868
00:53:15,505 --> 00:53:16,881
-Dad!
-Ji-ung.

869
00:53:19,426 --> 00:53:20,552
Yes, darling.

870
00:53:20,635 --> 00:53:22,345
My goodness, darling.

871
00:53:29,060 --> 00:53:31,479
I'm so upset.
What on earth are you wearing?

872
00:53:31,563 --> 00:53:32,605
Are you crazy?

873
00:53:33,356 --> 00:53:34,774
Excuse me.

874
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:38,028
Why are our children in this state?

875
00:53:38,111 --> 00:53:41,323
I looked into it a bit,
and you did all sorts of nonsense.

876
00:53:41,406 --> 00:53:43,616
You got them to do the dishes?
Even I don't!

877
00:53:43,700 --> 00:53:47,329
Also, I heard you put them
in the same space as murderers!

878
00:53:47,412 --> 00:53:49,331
As a human, how could you do that?

879
00:53:49,414 --> 00:53:54,210
How could you send children
as young as 14 years old to prison?

880
00:53:54,294 --> 00:53:56,087
Don't you know they're underage?

881
00:53:57,213 --> 00:53:58,214
Now.

882
00:54:00,300 --> 00:54:02,177
Do you know what this is?

883
00:54:02,927 --> 00:54:04,220
What is it?

884
00:54:06,348 --> 00:54:07,515
Tell them. What is it?

885
00:54:10,602 --> 00:54:13,646
They're just diet pills.

886
00:54:13,730 --> 00:54:16,399
The kids asked me
to get them for them, so I did.

887
00:54:16,483 --> 00:54:17,692
What's the problem?

888
00:54:26,743 --> 00:54:27,577
Oh my God.

889
00:54:28,161 --> 00:54:29,913
What are you doing? You must be crazy.

890
00:54:29,996 --> 00:54:31,414
Oh my goodness!

891
00:54:32,332 --> 00:54:34,501
What's the matter?

892
00:54:34,584 --> 00:54:35,919
I swallowed it.

893
00:54:36,002 --> 00:54:37,545
For God's sake.

894
00:54:37,629 --> 00:54:38,963
-Mom! What do I do?
-Oh my!

895
00:54:39,589 --> 00:54:41,966
Why? What's wrong? What?

896
00:54:42,050 --> 00:54:44,677
You said they're diet pills.
Don't you want to lose weight?

897
00:54:45,261 --> 00:54:46,429
What's wrong? Jesus!

898
00:54:48,681 --> 00:54:50,100
Mom, what do I do?

899
00:54:50,183 --> 00:54:52,310
-Mom!
-They're just supplements.

900
00:54:52,394 --> 00:54:53,561
That's enough.

901
00:54:55,730 --> 00:54:56,773
They're supplements?

902
00:54:57,357 --> 00:54:59,317
Shit, I'm fucked.

903
00:54:59,401 --> 00:55:01,444
You seem aware
these pills shouldn't be taken.

904
00:55:01,528 --> 00:55:04,197
-Mom, I nearly got fucked.
-Why? What's wrong?

905
00:55:04,280 --> 00:55:06,950
These pills,
the same shape as the ones he just took,

906
00:55:07,033 --> 00:55:09,536
are designer drugs containing phentermine.

907
00:55:11,704 --> 00:55:13,957
They were feeding them to their friends.

908
00:55:16,876 --> 00:55:19,254
Mom, I really didn't know.

909
00:55:19,337 --> 00:55:20,797
I didn't know what I was doing.

910
00:55:21,381 --> 00:55:22,215
Mom.

911
00:55:22,298 --> 00:55:23,550
He says he didn't know!

912
00:55:24,467 --> 00:55:26,469
They're juvenile offenders for a reason.

913
00:55:26,553 --> 00:55:31,099
Children have no idea
what consequences these things can have.

914
00:55:31,182 --> 00:55:35,770
That's why adults should protect
juvenile offenders.

915
00:55:35,854 --> 00:55:38,523
-Isn't that right? Aren't I right?
-What do kids know?

916
00:55:38,606 --> 00:55:39,983
-They're young.
-Deputy Bong.

917
00:55:41,109 --> 00:55:42,485
Please look here.

918
00:55:43,027 --> 00:55:47,490
This is evidence that they distributed
and sold these drugs to their friends.

919
00:55:48,575 --> 00:55:51,703
They have made
over 50 million won this way.

920
00:55:52,245 --> 00:55:53,246
It's huge, isn't it?

921
00:55:53,329 --> 00:55:54,414
MIN JI-UNG
56,131,893 WON

922
00:55:55,832 --> 00:55:58,710
Juvenile offenders
who should be protected?

923
00:55:59,461 --> 00:56:00,670
Sure.

924
00:56:00,753 --> 00:56:02,005
EVIDENCE OF ASSAULT BY MIN JI-UNG

925
00:56:02,088 --> 00:56:03,590
Then what about the victims here?

926
00:56:05,675 --> 00:56:06,801
Who will protect them?

927
00:56:08,887 --> 00:56:11,014
But they didn't know.

928
00:56:11,514 --> 00:56:15,018
It's not too late to teach them now.
Isn't that right, sir?

929
00:56:15,101 --> 00:56:17,562
-Let's pool money for the settlement.
-Yes, let's.

930
00:56:17,645 --> 00:56:19,606
We'll use it to compensate the victims.

931
00:56:20,106 --> 00:56:23,485
Then we just need to get the petitions
and submit them, don't we?

932
00:56:23,985 --> 00:56:24,986
That's right.

933
00:56:25,069 --> 00:56:26,571
We'll do everything necessary.

934
00:56:26,654 --> 00:56:29,240
-So please go easy on them, sir.
-Just this once…

935
00:56:29,324 --> 00:56:32,577
They're still young children
with their whole lives ahead of them.

936
00:56:32,660 --> 00:56:35,163
Shouldn't they be given a chance, sir?

937
00:56:35,246 --> 00:56:36,456
Shut up!

938
00:56:39,876 --> 00:56:42,128
"You must not harm others."

939
00:56:43,379 --> 00:56:45,507
"You must not hurt others."

940
00:56:47,675 --> 00:56:50,303
These are the things
you should have taught them.

941
00:56:52,680 --> 00:56:54,516
If you couldn't, the school should have.

942
00:56:56,434 --> 00:56:59,896
If the school couldn't,
society should have taught them.

943
00:57:01,523 --> 00:57:03,858
But everyone failed,
so the ERPB had to step in.

944
00:57:04,359 --> 00:57:06,402
At least the ERPB will teach them.

945
00:57:07,612 --> 00:57:09,989
When a person does wrong,
they will be punished!

946
00:57:10,490 --> 00:57:13,785
Perpetrators should never stand taller
than their victims!

947
00:57:19,874 --> 00:57:21,876
That's how they must take responsibility.

948
00:57:33,263 --> 00:57:35,098
Mom, do something.

949
00:57:35,890 --> 00:57:37,141
-Mom?
-Just a moment.

950
00:57:37,976 --> 00:57:41,688
He says he is truly repentant, sir.
I mean, Minister.

951
00:57:41,771 --> 00:57:42,647
I'm sorry.

952
00:57:43,231 --> 00:57:45,066
You won't ever do that again, will you?

953
00:57:45,149 --> 00:57:45,984
-No.
-No.

954
00:57:46,067 --> 00:57:47,986
I'm sorry! I'm really sorry!

955
00:57:48,069 --> 00:57:51,531
I won't ever do it again.
I have truly repented, sir.

956
00:57:51,614 --> 00:57:53,157
Please let me off this once.

957
00:57:53,241 --> 00:57:54,909
Please give me another chance.

958
00:57:54,993 --> 00:57:56,619
Please, I beg you.

959
00:57:57,203 --> 00:57:58,162
I really…

960
00:57:58,663 --> 00:58:01,374
-Please.
-Right, you should've repented like this.

961
00:58:01,457 --> 00:58:04,210
I really can't go back. I can't.

962
00:58:04,711 --> 00:58:06,796
But we're not the ones

963
00:58:08,381 --> 00:58:09,382
to forgive you.

964
00:58:53,092 --> 00:58:54,010
You guys…

965
00:58:56,971 --> 00:58:58,848
I will never forgive you.

966
00:59:02,644 --> 00:59:05,813
I never had a single day of peace,
all because of you.

967
00:59:07,398 --> 00:59:10,860
I was so terrified
that I couldn't even breathe.

968
00:59:12,612 --> 00:59:13,780
To me,

969
00:59:15,698 --> 00:59:16,866
school was hell.

970
00:59:20,036 --> 00:59:23,081
From now on, this place is hell,
and I'll make sure to find you.

971
00:59:23,164 --> 00:59:26,084
<i>Let's play hide and seek all day long.</i>

972
00:59:27,960 --> 00:59:30,672
Why should I run away
when you're the ones who did wrong?

973
00:59:31,589 --> 00:59:33,383
I want to go to school too!

974
00:59:33,883 --> 00:59:35,885
I want to graduate too!

975
00:59:35,968 --> 00:59:37,845
What the hell is she saying?

976
00:59:38,763 --> 00:59:40,014
I'm a juvenile offender.

977
00:59:40,723 --> 00:59:43,309
It means I'm allowed to kill you,
fucking bitch!

978
00:59:43,393 --> 00:59:45,311
Ji-ung! Oh my God!

979
00:59:53,069 --> 00:59:56,572
The parents' request
for the release of the children

980
00:59:57,865 --> 00:59:59,617
is hereby denied.

981
00:59:59,701 --> 01:00:00,827
No, wait…

982
01:00:00,910 --> 01:00:02,829
-Hereby denied?
-What do you mean, denied?

983
01:00:02,912 --> 01:00:04,080
What do you mean?

984
01:00:04,163 --> 01:00:07,166
The children will be taken back
to the juvenile prison.

985
01:00:07,250 --> 01:00:08,835
-No.
-What do you mean? No.

986
01:00:08,918 --> 01:00:10,002
-Mister!
-Dad!

987
01:00:10,086 --> 01:00:11,379
No!

988
01:00:15,007 --> 01:00:16,050
Mom! What do I do?

989
01:00:17,260 --> 01:00:18,511
Mom!

990
01:00:18,594 --> 01:00:20,096
Oh no, my baby!

991
01:00:21,556 --> 01:00:22,390
Ji-ung!

992
01:00:26,102 --> 01:00:28,396
My baby! Move aside for a second!

993
01:01:13,983 --> 01:01:15,860
Thank you.

994
01:01:17,528 --> 01:01:21,949
<i>From now on, the ERPB</i>
<i>will educate juvenile offenders.</i>

995
01:01:22,742 --> 01:01:26,704
Seventy years have passed,
yet there has only been empty talk.

996
01:01:27,371 --> 01:01:30,500
The juvenile system hasn't changed,
but crimes have increased.

997
01:01:30,583 --> 01:01:34,086
As a result, innocent students
are still suffering today.

998
01:01:34,170 --> 01:01:37,924
Since someone has to make changes,
the ERPB will step up.

999
01:01:38,925 --> 01:01:40,885
The law may exempt juvenile offenders,

1000
01:01:41,385 --> 01:01:44,514
but the education system will not.

1001
01:01:48,059 --> 01:01:50,520
Hey, babe!

1002
01:02:07,453 --> 01:02:08,663
Fuck.

1003
01:02:13,417 --> 01:02:14,252
Get inside.

1004
01:02:16,379 --> 01:02:18,422
If you did wrong, you should be punished.

1005
01:02:32,728 --> 01:02:33,813
I'm sorry.

1006
01:02:56,919 --> 01:02:57,753
Get inside.

1007
01:03:01,632 --> 01:03:03,801
Feel the victims' pain.

1008
01:03:04,385 --> 01:03:06,178
You'll learn a lot in there.

1009
01:03:15,104 --> 01:03:16,063
Get inside.

1010
01:03:16,731 --> 01:03:17,690
Get inside.

1011
01:03:21,903 --> 01:03:23,863
How long do we have to stay here?

1012
01:03:24,614 --> 01:03:25,907
Until you're of age.

1013
01:03:26,949 --> 01:03:28,284
After that,

1014
01:03:28,367 --> 01:03:30,703
the law will hold you accountable anyway.

1015
01:03:39,045 --> 01:03:41,255
Yun-jin, I'm sorry.

1016
01:03:41,339 --> 01:03:43,007
Yun-jin!

1017
01:03:43,090 --> 01:03:44,675
I'm sorry. I'll never do it again.

1018
01:03:44,759 --> 01:03:46,802
Please open the door, Yun-jin.

1019
01:03:47,929 --> 01:03:48,971
Yun-jin.

1020
01:03:59,440 --> 01:04:00,274
Good work, guys.

1021
01:04:00,358 --> 01:04:02,068
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

1022
01:04:02,151 --> 01:04:03,194
Thank you.

1023
01:04:09,867 --> 01:04:11,827
Are you sure this is enough?

1024
01:04:11,911 --> 01:04:13,120
Yes, sir.

1025
01:04:15,122 --> 01:04:16,540
I really missed this.

1026
01:04:17,583 --> 01:04:18,417
All right.

1027
01:04:20,461 --> 01:04:21,629
Thanks for helping me.

1028
01:04:22,213 --> 01:04:24,924
Not at all.
I offered to help in the first place.

1029
01:04:26,842 --> 01:04:28,010
But in return,

1030
01:04:28,886 --> 01:04:30,513
please promise me one thing.

1031
01:04:33,224 --> 01:04:35,476
Please make sure
no one ends up like me again.

1032
01:04:37,645 --> 01:04:39,855
I think the ERPB
will be able to manage that.

1033
01:04:46,195 --> 01:04:47,780
Can I really drink this?

1034
01:05:01,836 --> 01:05:03,087
Hey, juvenile offender.

1035
01:05:06,298 --> 01:05:07,133
Yes?

1036
01:05:07,800 --> 01:05:09,385
You know the BS gang boss, right?

1037
01:05:11,595 --> 01:05:13,264
But I didn't mention that thing.

1038
01:05:13,347 --> 01:05:15,141
-Not a single word.
-Well done.

1039
01:05:15,933 --> 01:05:18,394
But our boss tends to be quite cautious.

1040
01:05:18,477 --> 01:05:20,438
-Do you know what I mean?
-Yes.

1041
01:05:22,148 --> 01:05:23,232
Goodbye.

1042
01:07:01,247 --> 01:07:04,208
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

